<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="subplot">
  <info>
    <pubdate>$LastChangedDate$</pubdate>
  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>subplot</refname>
    <refpurpose> divide a graphics window into a matrix of sub-windows</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>subplot(m,n,p)
subplot(mnp)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Arguments</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>m,n,p</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>positive integers</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>mnp</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>an integer with decimal notation <literal>mnp</literal></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
    subplot(m,n,p) or subplot(mnp) breaks the graphics window
    into an m-by-n matrix of sub-windows and selects the p-th sub-window
    for drawing  the current plot.  The number of a sub-window into the
    matrices is counted row by row ie the sub-window corresponding to element
    (i,j) of the matrix has number (i-1)*n + j.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[ 
subplot(221)
plot2d()
subplot(222)
plot3d()
subplot(2,2,3)
param3d()
subplot(2,2,4)
hist3d()
 ]]></programlisting>
  </refsection>
